<h2><font face="Verdana">Collaboration with other 
applications</font> </h2>
<p><font face="Verdana">Adapt has the capability to work with 
other translation applications. This capacity means that you have the option to 
use other tools (applications) along with Adapt It in your translation projects. 
This option means that you can take advantage of the strengths of each tool to 
speed the process and create the produce an excellent final product.</font> </p>
<p><font face="Verdana">Adapt It has always had the capability 
to use <a 
href="../Consistent_Changes/Consistent_changes_overview.htm">Consistent 
Changes</a> and <a 
href="../../User_Interface/Menu_Bar/Tools_Menu/SIL_converters_overview.htm">SIL 
Converters</a>. With the release of version 6.0 and higher, Adapt It now has the 
capability to&nbsp;work with <a 
href="http://paratext.ubs-translations.org/about/pt">Paratext</a> and <a 
href="https://sites.google.com/site/bibledit/">Bibledit</a>. These 
applications have strong capabilites to prepare transactions for publication thus 
adding to the capabilities of Adapt It. </font> </p>
<p><font face="Verdana">The collaboration process for Paratext (PT) and Bibledit 
(BE)&nbsp;is different than&nbsp;that of Consistent Changes and SIL Converters. 
With the latter two applications, the change is embedded&nbsp;with Adapt It 
and&nbsp;works as part of the&nbsp;adaptation process.&nbsp;Paratext and 
Bibledit operate outside of Adapt It.&nbsp; </font>&nbsp;<font face="Verdana">The following diagram shows the 
interaction.</font></p>
<p><img style="WIDTH: 43.14%; HEIGHT: 50%" border="0" hspace="0" 
src="adapt_it_collaboration.png" width="50%" height="50%"></p>
<p><font face="Verdana">The 
collaboration process works like this:</font>    </p>
<ol>
<li>
<p class="BodyText"><font face="Verdana">The source document is prepared in a PT or 
  BE project.</font>     </p>
<li>
<p class="BodyText"><font face="Verdana">The user establishes the links between Adapt It and the 
  source project and a target project in PT or BE. 
  </font>  </p>
  <li>
  <p class="BodyText"><font face="Verdana">The user opens the adaptation process in 
  Adapt It. Adapt It then:</font></p>
  <ol>
    <li>
    <p class="BodyText"><font face="Verdana">Reads in the source text from the 
    Source project</font></p>
    <li>
    <p class="BodyText"><font face="Verdana">  Makes&nbsp;user adaptations in&nbsp;the 
    normal manner</font></p>
    <li>
    <p class="BodyText"><font face="Verdana">When the session is concluded, stores 
    the results of the&nbsp;adaptations&nbsp;into the target 
    project.</font></p></li></ol>
  <li>
  <p class="BodyText"><font face="Verdana">When the adaptation project is complete, 
  the user prepares the translation for publication using PT or 
  BE.</font></p></li></ol>
<p class="BodyText">&nbsp;</p>
